WRITING.TEXT:
b'MPB is caused by excess DHT making it to the scalp which manifests as a thick kinda substance that clogs your hair sacks basically. Your blood supply then is not able to give these sacks the oxygen they need to grow, and your hairs will diffuse over time and fall out due to hypoxia.

Finasteride tackles the problem by basically reducing total DHT by inhibiting the enzyme responsible for testosterone to DHT derivation in your body, therefore less thick hormone manifest gets in these sacks.

Minoxidil tackles the problem of hypoxia specifically, basically forcing your body to work a bit harder to send more oxygen to the scalp.

To answer your question. Combination typically provides best results, however both can work on their own, just in different ways.'

Financially things differ between associations.-Members pay contribution to the association and/or often also to their dispute.-All the big associations have a contract with some beer company that allows them to offer extremely low prices for the beer, as long as they consume enough of it consistently.-Most associations have one building for the association (where they all get together and drink basically), and some will have seperate buildings for the disputes. These buildings are either owned by the disputes themselves or by the student association. Usually these buildings were bought long ago before the prices were as high as they are now. Some larger disputes apparently also have a beer contract as they are able to meet the quota on their own, so they have a tap in their house.  


Employment/work differs a bit across all of them. Associations like ''het corps'' tend to be able to afford their own employees to clean the buildings and pay bartenders, dj's etc. Other associations make their first years do some of the work, or have commissions with members do the work with some benefit in return (reduction of membership fee/ free drinks) etc, or do a combination of the above."

WRITING.TITLE: b' '
WRITING.TEXT:
b'As a user of both pb100\xe2\x80\x99s and the bb2 ill explain the difference from my experience.

The bb2 has a better bluetooth connection at bluetooth 5, this makes a big difference imo because with the pb100 i can hardly walk away and the signal would drop. The pb110 should have this fixed though as it also has bt5.

The boombox 2 is also ipx7 which makes it more durable when using it near a pool, and you dont have to worry about it in the rain.

Battery life is also much longer on the bb2, i\xe2\x80\x99ve lost count how many hours ive been able to bring it on max volume. 

Along with its more portable form, this is what made the bb2 more expensive than the partyboxes.

Soundwise the bb2 will increase the bass eq up untill it reaches 80% volume, and then will increase the mids and highs from 80-100%. The reason they do this is because mids and highs travel better at outdoor use in comparison to bass. Though of course, quality wise it isnt the best, although you should consider the bb2 only is 60-80w, and the performance ratios for that power is pushed to reach that volume.

Imo the dsp and the soundstage of the partyboxes is better. WRITING.TITLE: b' '
WRITING.TEXT:
b"We gaan er in de huidige modellen van uit dat een positieve PCR test een besmetting meet. Enige probleem hiermee is dat een PCR test niet actief virus kan meten, maar slechts aantoont of er genetische deeltjes van het virus aanwezig zijn in de neus/keel. Je zou dus ook met dode virusdeeltjes in je neus/keelholtes positief moeten testen via PCR. Dit is overigens ook de reden dat sommige landen (vooral zuid amerika nu vgm), je ook met antigeen tests laten reizen als je positief blijft testen op corona. 

Het logistieke probleem hier met gevaccineerden is dat aanwezige deeltjes niet per se betekenen dat de persoon ziek wordt, of uberhaubt andere mensen kan besmetten met deze deeltjes. Dit probleem versterkt zich met gevaccineerden, omdat we er vanuit gaan dat je immuunsysteem deze deeltjes in de meeste gevallen direct kan doden (dit bedoelde ik met ziekteverloop, alhoewel het miss niet echt ziekte te noemen is). De aanwezigheid van de deeltjes (positieve pcrtests) betekent dus langzaam steeds minder voor degene die gevaccineerd zijn. Het onderzoek hierin moet nog uitgebreid worden, maar je kan er wel degelijk vanuit gaan dat een positieve besmetting van een gevaccineerd individueel anders opweegt tegenover besmetting van een niet gevaccineerde. Het gevaar in de eerste instantie was overigens ziekenhuisopnames en niet besmetting; besmetting zal je namelijk altijd blijven zien. 

In mijn eerste comment wou ik de suggestie doen om een variabele als ziekenhuisopnames mee te nemen, om te controleren op ratio gevaccineerden/niet gevaccineerden. Je moet namelijk 'iets' doen om deze PCRtesten nog enigzins te 'controleren'. Ik las wel een goed tegenargument, namelijk dat de IC cijfers 2 weken achterlopen. Daar ben ik het wel mee eens. Een alternatief is dan om vaccinatiegraad mee te nemen en wat statistische trucjes toe te passen."

b'Bb2 got an update a while back and it has a more clear sound now imo. Nevertheless the passive radiators still make my house rumble whenever i turn it on. I\xe2\x80\x99d say its more ideal for outdoor use. Main reason why I bought it over the hyperboom was the lower frequency reproduction, and with the water resistance rating and the overall rugged design it would last me quite a while (i replaced a bluetooth speaker that probably lasted me 8 to 9 years; that still worked!).
Hyperboom has a wider soundstage due to its square design and is feature packed; has more port options eq options etc. is less wide so its easier to fit in a room somewhere. Just doesnt have the ipx 7 rating.
Both speakers have pairing options though JBL, as you may know, only lets you pair to the partyboost generation speakers. The pairing protocol for JBL does have a lot better range though.

You can watch a binaural video from oluv\xe2\x80\x99s gadgets comparing the two, gives you a decent impression of the audio. The update on the jbl accentuated the mids a bit, so the range is a bit better now.'

WRITING.TITLE: b' '
WRITING.TEXT:
b"I mix techno very differently than house. For some reason with techno I kind of make these artificial drops with my EQ's to bring in the drop of the next song, and then keep the first song in until the mid and high bands are properly introduced, works very nicely and sounds great on large speaker setups.  


For house I apply all sorts of tricks, its really just a fast mixing for me. Sometimes I will loop part of the first track when the second drop is about to come in and keep cutting that loop short, and perhaps applying a filter until that second drop hits.   
Another thing you can do is just go from drop to drop with the same EQ trick you might do for techno. When i'm playing house or for a club in general, I think its important to be able to switch tracks at any point. It might not sound technically perfect, but to get a crowd going you need to make sure the music selection is perfect. Sometimes I will introduce a melody of one track on top of the master and just see if the crowd likes it before I decide to throw that in."

WRITING.TEXT:
b"My guess is that this issue is probably due to the environment that you are installing the modules on.

If you install python through anaconda for example, then your python version that you are editing on with your IDE is in the conda environment. This also means that you will need to pip install everything on that environment.

In my case, this means that I must first type in -conda activate in my terminal before I pip install any modules that I want to run on anaconda python. In powershell I think you can just do `conda activate env-name`, but this will all depend on the environment you're using (my example is for anaconda). If you're not using anaconda you will obviously need to use a different command to get into the right python environment.  


I also am not sure how experienced you are. Are you importing the modules correctly in your code? Examples would help us diagnose the issue :)"

WRITING.TITLE: b' '
WRITING.TEXT:
b"I have a charge 5. I basically wanted the smaller size for portability, for sound I do think the Xtreme 3 is a better option, but of course that comes at a price. Its basically the difference between mono and stereo and driver setup. Xtreme has two woofers and two tweeters, and the charge 5 has one wide woofer and a tweeter.   
Thing is though that imo the speaker separation on small speakers isn't that noticeable. 

Don't consider getting the charge 4 over the 5, the 5 is definitely a good upgrade over the 4 in terms of travel (due to mid high focus its less energy costly to get sound to travel in comparison to low frequencies) and mids/high clarity.

 With the Xtreme you can definitely consider getting the 2 over the 3. Imo my main consideration is the connect+ generation ending as you mentioned in your title. We will have to wait and see if the next generation of JBL speakers will continue with Partyboost, and hope that they won't change to a new protocol again. 

When comparing Xtreme 2 to the charge 5 it really depends on what you prefer. In my opinion the mids and highs are more clear on the Charge 5 compared to the Xtreme 2, but then again, the Xtreme series has that stereo separation and an AC mode that the charge doesn't have. Another benefit to the Xtreme 2 is that it has an aux port. I think the bass performance on the Xtreme 2 is also better than on the Charge 5, mainly due to driver size. But then again you will also need to consider whether you prefer Partyboost over connect plus. 

The only real difference between Partyboost and Connect+ is that Partyboost is more stable. When I pair my speakers I have no problem carrying them to other rooms for a multi-room setup with Partyboost (around 70m without walls and with source device close to main). Connect+ will cut off quite a bit quicker (35m)."

Do note that an NLTK object is not a string object (if i remember correctly) , so you will need to convert your objects here and there to get them working with the rest of your code."

WRITING.TITLE: b' '
WRITING.TEXT: b"I don't know this program but I can say the following:  \n5x5 is just 5x5, no rep range increase should be the goal necessarily, but the movement should remain difficult to accomplish at 5x5. Once it has gotten easy, you move on to a heavier variation, and if you want to do proper step loading, you can have the transition week be a period of light exercise before you move onto heavier weight. If this is the goal, then you should aim for about 3 or 4 weeks of 5x5 and 1 week of rest, and then reset the week after with a heavier variation/load.  \nI'm not sure on your current level, but as a warning, I shall say that I do not recommend this for beginners. I am a firm believer in that beginners should first focus on acquiring basic foundational strength with enough volume (about 10 rep range) before moving on to specific strength training. Mainly because moving into strength rep range too early leaves you at very high risk for injury. I'm assuming that this is the reason why this program starts with this beginner routine, but I just want to stress the importance of having a good foundation first."

WRITING.TITLE: b' '
WRITING.TEXT:
b'Mind body connections I guess.   
One of the first lectures I had when studying communication science was from a professor (Lourens de Vries) who had lived with the Korowai people in Papua New Guinea to study their language system. He explained that instead of counting from one hand to the next, and thus with 10 fingers in total and a 10 word counting system, these people counted from one pinkie from the next. They would start with the hands, go to the forearm, and go around the whole body until they ended up at the number 25 back at their other hand. This was a closed system, and these people never had the need to count to a higher number than that.  
These types of counting systems are more common in Papuan languages, there are even differences between men and women in some languages. The Yupna men for example, include the left testicle, the penis, and the right testicle in their number system, and if I remember correctly men can count higher than women in that language.  
Over time however, it is predicted that more and more of these counting systems disappear. Because when these people are introduced to an open system, they generally adopt this over their own.'

WRITING.TITLE: b' '
WRITING.TEXT: b"u/HornyCaspar   \nThe amount of fat you gain depends on the ratio's of protein/carbs/fat you eat. If you want to gain muscle, you will need to be eating at caloric surplus as you mention. You should then really just be eating about 1g of protein per lbs of bodyweight and stay at around 200 to 300 calories above maintenance. The other ratios of carbs/fat don't really matter that much, but realistically they should be at approximately 40%/30% respectively . This is a lean bulk, so you will stay lean, but still in surplus. Basically adding more muscle to your frame will require you to gain some fat, but at these ratios its still pretty minimal and can easily be shredded off whenever you want to look like a mean lean chicken breast."

WRITING.TITLE: b' '
WRITING.TEXT:
b"Yeah with pull ups you see all sorts of forms, and from my experience I really think it depends on the kind of lifter you're looking at.

Generally I think locking out the elbows is good, and is good form. Some individuals with bodybuilding aspirations might not fully lock out to alter development of their muscle bellies or for time under tension reasons, but for a pull up as a compound exercise I would argue that this is just dumb. An approach like that would maybe be useful for a bicep curl for example, or any isolatable exercise. I think most frequently though, the people who do this are just chasing reps, and therefore not fully extending to an elbow lockout in an active hang.

The benefit that you get from staying in an active hang vs dead hang is the time under tension; giving you hypertrophy benefits. Additionally the scapula is constantly engaged, and if constantly activated with chest pointing to bar will benefit transfer to front lever.

The benefit that you get from a dead hang position is that you are training scapula activation. For some calisthenics exercises, like the OAP this is very important.

So to conclude, both lock-out active hang or dead hang are good, just for different reasons. Don't under extend, that just seems stupid to me.  


EDIT: Btw with L sit pull ups, I think active hang is generally better since your nervous system is working in the  'dead hang' anyways, so it isn't really 'dead', though I wanted to generalise my reply for pull ups in general."

WRITING.TITLE: b' '
WRITING.TEXT:
b"Many factors can contribute to this. Of course being well rested and giving your body the time it needs helps, but diet is generally the main contributor.  
\-Basically eating a low amount of carbohydrates for a few days, and then suddenly eating a lot of carbs is called carb loading. This will significantly increase the glycogen stores in your muscles and as a result they have more energy in the work out. For me personally, being loaded in this way makes a night and day difference in my performance. 

\-Do you drink caffeinated drinks? When I drink red bull before a work-out (I don't recommend doing this, the stuff ain't good for you lol) there is also a pretty big difference in my performance. Theres some academic literature arguing that the high caffeine dose contributing to increased heart rate/blood flow improves performance, this is also the reason they put the stuff in pre-workout."

WRITING.TEXT: b'So a 3:1 step loading schema here would work as follows. Lets say 5x5 20kg weighted pull is very difficult for you. Dominik sky has a pretty good explanation on this here

Ik zou denk ik ook echt niet geweten hebben of ik toen een meisje of een jongen wou zijn. Door deze vraag continu te representeren krijg je een groep kinderen die hier over gaan twijfelen op een leeftijd waar ze dat normaal niet doen.   
Het is lastig, maar aangezien dit maar voor approxima 1% van de bevolking van belang is denk ik dat je er pas over moet gaan nadenken als er duidelijke gedrags en neurologische redenen zijn voor zo\xc2\xb4n besluit, en zou het het beste dus het beste door middel van experts consultancy overwogen moeten worden, ipv door de media continu ter aandacht gebracht moeten worden.  
Politiek zou dit betekenen dat psychologische ondersteuning toegankelijker moet worden, op die manier kan het \xc2\xb4\xc2\xb4normaal\xc2\xb4\xc2\xb4 worden om naar een psycholoog te gaan die kan bepalen of hier uberhaubt over nagedacht moet worden of niet."
